    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.73/4a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-08T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>106. The Department is informed that the President of Cuba has recently
                    authorized the Secretary of the Interior to grant a concession to the Western
                    Union Telegraph Company to lay a cable from Cojimar to the island of Barbados.
                    You are instructed to telegraph as soon as possible the date of the Executive
                    Decree containing this authorization and to inform Department whether concession
                    to the Company has actually been granted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
